 src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The class doesnt need to accel at anything.</span><hr size=1> Wezloc<br>
<br>
There are a few spells that permit Magicians and Wizards to instakill mobs.<br>
<br>
Magicians - Banishment (&quot;assassinate&quot; vs summoned)<br>
Wizards - Disintegration (&quot;assassinate&quot; vs all creatures)<br>
<br>
Of course, these spells do have a costly reagent, and have a level cap, but there are such spells in existance. You also have to look at a classes role and &quot;ideal environment&quot;. Rogues have to attack from the back for this uber assassinate proc. Usually, that's fairly easy for them to do. Rogues bring little else BUT damage to their group. Magicians bring direct damage, melee damage, boosts for others to do damage (other casters), indirect damage as well as mana regen, and occasionally, pull safety. It's so much fun to have these two mobs that stand still where they lay after they have aggro on something and it dies/flees. Of all the crazy schemes that I heard, the suggested one of &quot;Just aggro them, and run far away. I will summon you back to us.&quot; Turned out to be the safest, best, and easiest to impliment. This is against unmezzable, uncharmable mobs. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
